cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use tokenfit in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "tokenfit: Heuristic token-count estimation for LLM context windows"
version: "0.2.0"
date-released: "2026-04-30"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/vdeshmukh203/tokenfit"
authors:
  - family-names: Deshmukh
    given-names: Vaibhav
keywords:
  - large language models
  - tokenisation
  - natural language processing
  - developer tools
  - Python
abstract: >
  tokenfit is a lightweight, pure-Python library that estimates token counts for
  text and chat-style message lists without making any API calls or loading any
  model artefact. It uses per-family character-to-token ratios covering all
  major commercial LLM families and always rounds up so reported counts never
  under-report.
